Curtain: Set a plan, implement, and look at whether structural change can benefit your business. #reaclick
Curtain: Think differently - if your old methods aren't getting the result you want, have a go at something new. #reaclick
Curtain: A good business doesn't rest on its laurels. Ask "where can we go forward from here"? #reaclick
Curtain: Strong leadership is vital, and has to be present whether out in the field on your own or working as a team. #reagroup
Curtain: Making a customer feel good doesn't necessarily take a lot of effort, it's just about implementing the right practices. #reaclick
Curtain: Don't forget the importance of the offline experience for customers - analog's important too. #reaclick
Next speaker is Paul Curtain, Managing Director of Place Estate Agents. #reaclick
Carroll: "The digital interview has arrived" - people assess agents/agencies based on their online research. #reaclick
Carroll: Don't forget mobile - check how your brand appears on mobile at least once a week, make sure you look your best. #reaclick
Carroll: We're becoming increasingly mobile, and wearable tech is likely to be the next major step in this journey. #reaclick
Next speaker is @realestate_au's Head of Sales Steve Carroll, talking about future trends #reaclick
Fraser: The more peak moments you make for a customer, the more referrals you'll get. #reaclick
Fraser: We don't remember the entire experience, just particularly memorable moments. #reaclick
Fraser: 4 feelings that matter most in vendor's property journey: security, reassurance, control and confidence. #reaclick
Fraser: Emotions are important - customers are driven by how they feel about things, and emotion drives memory. #reaclick
Fraser: The amount of mental space and attention people have to give is small, so it's fundamental to be memorable #reaclick
Fraser: Buyers/vendors who have a bad agent experience talk about it on social media and reputation can be damaged very quickly. #reaclick
Fraser: In the past ten years, businesses gone from asking how to do same things to more people to how to stand out from others. #reaclick
Tables discussing how vendors/buyers have changed: more informed, online, expecting fast responses. #reaclick
Fraser: Everything in the world's getting faster, people are increasingly time poor. #reaclick
